## Locked Game Mechanics (Phase 5.5)

### Stats (7)
STR, DEX, CON, INT, WIS, CHA, LCK

### Roll Formula
```
d20 + stat_modifier + skill_rank + proficiency_bonus ≥ DC
```
- Proficiency bonus: +2 (when skill_rank ≥ 3)
- Nat 20 = auto-success + double damage
- Nat 1 = auto-fail + complication

### DC Scale
- Easy: 8
- Medium: 12
- Hard: 16
- Extreme: 20
- Legendary: 24+

### HP/Mana Formulas
- HP: base (archetype) + CON_mod × level
- Mana: 8 + INT_mod × level (Mage only)

## Test Requirements

### Must Pass Before Any Commit
```bash
cd backend

# Phase 7 - Dice rolls (expected: 25/25)
python3 tests/run_dice_full_wiring_checks.py

# Phase 8 - Combat system (expected: 12/12)
python3 tests/test_phase8_combat.py

# Death system (expected: 5/5)
python3 tests/test_game_engine_death.py

# Solo death (expected: 48/48)
python3 tests/test_solo_death.py
```

## Common Patterns

### Adding New API Endpoint
1. Create route in `backend/app/api/[module].py`
2. Add to router in `backend/app/main.py`
3. Write test in `backend/tests/test_[module].py`
4. Test manually via curl or frontend
5. Update Coda documentation

### Modifying Database
1. Write migration in `backend/app/migrations_admin.py`
2. Test migration on copy of DB first
3. Update models if needed
4. Write test that verifies schema
5. Document in Coda Architecture Map

### Frontend Changes
1. Modify HTML/CSS/JS in `frontend/`
2. Test in browser at https://aigm-prod.studio-colorbox.com/
3. Check browser console for errors
4. Verify mobile responsiveness
5. Update Coda if UI flow changed

## Debugging Checklist

- [ ] Read full error message (don't skim)
- [ ] Check Loki logs (if observability running)
- [ ] Verify DB state with sqlite3
- [ ] Test LLM connectivity separately
- [ ] Check git diff for unexpected changes
- [ ] Ask human before making assumptions

